observation1: The letter I indicated show to be much different from each other on the two notes. The "y" in the bottom note is written in one shot, no lift of the pen, while the "y" written by the robber is written through separated pen strokes. The lowercase "g"'s differ in that the top written sample has a more extended and exaggerated end of the "g" while the bottom sample is not as exaggerated. Finally, the letter "t"'s differ in that the ones written in the sample on the bottom have a perpendicular stroke to the vertical portion of the t, more towards the middle or bottom of the letter, while in the first sample provided the stroke is more towards the top of the vertical line. Therefore, they are not the same, similar yes, but noticeably different.
